    {
      "id": "318b627f177b28f7680f5e68df4f51db8df2c1cf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-31 19:08:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI'm not against this landing, but I suspect a lot more might be able to be removed.\n\nMike, what is your thought on whether the whole of *fid2dentry() could be removed, along with the dead code in llog_lvfs_open()?  I suppose all of llog_lvfs_* could be removed if the MGS is moved over to OSD API and llog_osd_ops.  Do you have a patch for that already?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3a9bf424a2e9b367b74b0ed265a3017358110021",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-31 19:19:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas you can find the patch for the mgs port at http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5049",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "654ee66c7867aec1801f0843d6905ccae386d70a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-01 12:58:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: No score\n\nThe obd_fid2denty function is used only for llog_lvfs.Once the patch for LU-2059 lands llog_lvfs can go away. So is this patch really needed at this point.",
